  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Contributing to the defence of the campesino territory in Tolima</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project seeks to promote the guarantee and respect of the rights of small-scale farmers in Cajamarca, Tolima department in decisions affecting their territories. Peasant/small scale-farming communities in the municipality of Cajamarca are threatened by the installation of the La Colosa mining project. The main economic activity in this regions is agriculture. The region has been recognized as Colombia&apos;s largest pantry of agro-food production, as well as for being a region with strategic ecosystems of enormous water and biodiversity wealth, which are key to facing the effects of climate change.</narrative>
  </description>
